<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-vivid-red-color has-text-color has-link-c=
olor wp-elements-f0b49ce40793b0d4de2adc5ee9fc5160"><strong>Definition: Mill=
ibar (mbar)</strong></h2>



<p>A millibar (symbol: mbar) is a unit of pressure commonly used in meteoro=
logy to describe atmospheric pressure. It is equal to one-thousandth of a b=
ar, which is a metric unit of pressure.</p><div class=3D"qgyfs6937642bab413=
